node.text:
We have a broad coalition of activists, organizers, and elected officials pushing for a Civilian Climate Corps.

And together, we will work to make it a reality.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer and Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo speak at a GlobalFoundries event in New York, July 19, 2021

node.text:
I'm proud to stand with @secraimondo to announce a second GlobalFoundries factory to NY—& thousands of jobs!

I worked to pass $52B in the US Innovation & Competitiveness Act—and my Endless Frontier Act—to help grow good-paying construction jobs.

It's time for the House to pass it.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer participates in Suitcase Sunday, July 18, 2021.

node.text:
I was proud to join @WitnessToMI, @AdrienneEAdams1, and more than 50 incredible formerly incarcerated small business owners this weekend in Queens.

I'm proud we restored Pell Grants for formerly incarcerated people, and we'll keep working for criminal justice reform measures in the Senate.

node.text:
I was proud to join the Brooklyn Good Trouble Vigil for Democracy with @SenatorMyrie, @NewYorkStateAG, @RepYvetteClarke, @RabbiRachelTimoner, @RobertMWaterman, @CommonCauseNY, and more to honor John Lewis’s life and legacy.

The fight in the U.S. Senate to protect voting rights will continue.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer celebrates the Buffalo Bills.

node.text:
Happy #716Day to #BillsMafia and WNYers everywhere. Training Camp starts in two weeks.

Go Bills!

node.accessibility_caption: A tweet from Senator Schumer reads: “Democrats delivered the #ChildTaxCredit for families. And it’s a big f-ing deal.”

node.text:
Democrats delivered the #ChildTaxCredit for families.

And it’s a big f-ing deal.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer speaks on the Senate floor with a chart showing that every Republican voted against expanding the Child Tax Credit. (July 15, 2021)

node.text:
Republicans claim to be the party of tax cuts. But it’s really just for the wealthy and well-connected.

Democrats are sending the checks for the #ChildTaxCredit to America’s families.

When you see that check: Remember that every single Republican voted no.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer and President Biden in the U.S. Capitol, July 14, 2021.

node.text:
The landmark budget resolution that Senate Budget Democrats reached agreement on will pave the way to fight climate change and provide the most significant support for American families since the New Deal.

And that’s exactly what the Senate Democratic Majority is going to do.

node.accessibility_caption: Senator Schumer, Senator Wyden, and Senator Booker hold a press conference on the Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act, July 14, 2021.

node.text:
The War on Drugs has really been a war on people, especially people of color.

I’m proud to stand today with @RonWyden and @CoryBooker to release a discussion draft of the Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act.

It’s our legislative proposal to end the federal prohibition on marijuana and repair damage done by the War on Drugs.
